Topic: PGT, HGT & FGT (Outdoor Group Tasks) 🧗‍♂️🔥

👉 This is where real leadership is tested in action
👉 Not talking… DOING matters here

1️⃣ What are PGT, HGT, FGT?

These are group obstacle tasks conducted by GTO:

PGT → Progressive Group Task
HGT → Half Group Task
FGT → Final Group Task

👉 Goal: Cross obstacles using team + planning

🧗 Example of Group Obstacles
2️⃣ Basic Rules (VERY IMPORTANT)

You’ll be given:

Helping materials:
Rope
Plank
Log
⚠️ Rules:

❌ Don’t touch ground (out of bounds)
❌ Follow color rules (white, red, blue)
❌ Use materials properly

👉 GTO checks how you handle constraints

3️⃣ PGT (Progressive Group Task)

👉 Full group (8–10 members)
👉 Obstacles increase in difficulty

What to do:
Give ideas
Help physically
Support team
4️⃣ HGT (Half Group Task)

👉 Group divided into 2

💥 More chances to speak & lead

👉 GTO focuses more on:

Your contribution
Your initiative
5️⃣ FGT (Final Group Task)

👉 Same as PGT but last task

💥 Final impression matters here

6️⃣ How to Perform (STEP-BY-STEP)
🔹 Step 1: Observe obstacle
Understand structure
Think quickly
🔹 Step 2: Give idea

👉 Speak clearly:
“Let’s place plank here and use rope support”

🔹 Step 3: Execute
Help others cross
Stay active
🔹 Step 4: Motivate team

👉 Encourage:
“Come on, you can do it!”

🧠 GOLDEN RULE

👉 Action + Teamwork = Selection

7️⃣ Common Mistakes

❌ Standing silent
❌ Shouting without logic
❌ Not helping physically
❌ Breaking rules

8️⃣ PRO STRATEGY (SELECTION SECRET)

👉 Show these qualities:

Initiative
Cooperation
Leadership
Energy

💥 Don’t try to be hero
💥 Be team leader

9️⃣ Important Behavior Tips

✅ Stay energetic
✅ Be polite
✅ Listen to others
✅ Give logical ideas
✅ Help weakest member

10️⃣ Practice Task (Mental Training)

Imagine:

👉 You have:

1 rope
1 plank

👉 Task:
Cross a gap without touching ground

💭 Think:

How will you plan?
How will you lead?
🧠 SECRET TIP

👉 GTO is not checking:

Strength ❌
👉 He is checking:
Participation + thinking + teamwork ✅
